channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Biden makes the case for democracy after meeting with Zelensky
item.description: President Joe Biden apologized to Volodymyr Zelensky on Friday for aid delays from the US, telling the Ukrainian leader "we're not going to walk away from you."

item.title: Apollo 8 astronaut William Anders dies at 90
item.description: Apollo 8 astronaut William Anders has died at 90 years old, NASA administrator Bill Nelson said on Friday.

item.title: Day 5 of Hunter Biden's federal gun trial
item.description: Hunter Biden's trial on gun charges is underway in Delaware. The president's son faces three charges in the case brought by the special counsel. Follow here for the latest live news updates.

item.title: Manhattan DA agrees to testify in Congress, but likely not until Trump is sentenced
item.description: Manhattan District Attorney Alvin Bragg has agreed to testify before a Republican-controlled congressional subcommittee, but likely not until after former President Donald Trump is sentenced in July

item.title: William Anders, former Apollo 8 astronaut, dies in plane crash
item.description: William Anders, who snapped one of the most iconic images of the space age, was killed when his small plane went down off the coast of Washington state.

item.title: Key takeaways from the blowout May jobs report
item.description: The US economy added a whopping 272,000 jobs in May, far more than expected. The unemployment rate rose to 4% from 3.9%.

item.title: RFK Jr. files new petition in Nevada amid legal battle over ballot access
item.description: As Kennedy scrambles to gain ballot access in Nevada, some Democratic Party leaders worry he may siphon votes from President Biden in the key battleground state.

item.title: June 6, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: Dozens of people were killed in an Israeli airstrike on a United Nations-run school in central Gaza, authorities said, in an attack that CNN analysis found was conducted with a US-made weapon.
